      },
      "date": "2023-10-16 14:56:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> These functions are still declared in libcfs_cpu.h. Should they be in a LNet specific (new or existing) header?\n> \n> Also, this code seems closely related to libcfs_cpu.c, which seems used more widely in Lustre modules. Are you thinking of moving that to LNet too?\n\nYes. In fact I plan to in the next patch merge lib-mem.c into lib-cpt.c. I will move the header at a latter date since its more CPT related.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
