      },
      "date": "2023-11-01 01:02:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> Please also move the function declarations out of libcfs/include/libcfs/libcfs_cpu.h into some lnet include file.\n\nI plan to when I move libcfs_cpu.c next. One step at a time :-)\n\n> Ideally lib-mem.c would not include anything from libcfs .... though maybe we aren't there yet.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "155c66b17fb3cc4c38693f901299ae1fb3be2ec1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2023-11-01 03:12:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n\n> I plan to when I move libcfs_cpu.c next. One step at a time :-)\n\n\"One step at a time\" is good, but each step should be forwards.  Having declarations and code in unrelated places is a step backwards.\nSometimes it is optimal to have intermediate steps that are not pure improvements, but in those cases the commit message must spell out why there is a temporary regression.\nBut it don't think it is needed in this case.  Just create the new files in lnet, and move the desired content out of libcfs into those files.\nIt would make sense to delay renaming function to remove the \"libcfs\" from the name because that touches a different set of files.  But I don't think baby steps help.\nBut if you *really* want the baby-steps, please explain the plan in the commit message.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
